    "what_description": "Angelica sinensis is a perennial plant native to China, belonging to the family Apiaceae. It grows up to 2 meters in height, with a single stem bearing compound leaves consisting of 3-5 leaflets, each 3-10 cm long. The leaves are dark green, lanceolate, and serrated with a prominent midrib. The plant produces small, white or greenish flowers in an umbel, which is 10-20 cm in diameter, and is rich in nectar, attracting pollinators. The roots of Angelica sinensis are harvested for medicinal use, valued for their antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and hepatoprotective properties.",
