    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Angelica sinensis are its antioxidant properties, which help protect the body from oxidative stress and damage caused by free radicals. This is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, such as sinensiside and ligustilide, which exhibit strong free radical scavenging activity. Furthermore, Angelica sinensis has anti-inflammatory properties, which are mainly due to the presence of saponins, including angelan and acetyl-angelan, that can modulate the inflammatory response by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Additionally, this plant has cardioprotective effects, which are likely due to its ability to inhibit platelet aggregation and improve blood lipid profiles, as well as its antioxidant properties. Its analgesic and antimicrobial properties are also notable, with volatile oils, such as bornyl acetate and eugenol, contributing to its analgesic and antimicrobial activities.",
