    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Angelica sinensis are ligustilide, a sesquiterpene lactone with anti-inflammatory and antispasmodic properties, butylphthalide, a sesquiterpene with neuroprotective effects, ferulic acid, a phenolic acid with antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, coumarins, a class of compounds with anticoagulant and anti-inflammatory properties, and phenolic acids, including ferulic acid, which have been shown to scavenge free radicals and inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines, all of which contribute to the plant's ability to promote cardiovascular health, alleviate menopausal symptoms, and reduce inflammation and oxidative stress. Ligustilide has been found to relax smooth muscle, inhibit platelet aggregation, and reduce the production of pro-inflammatory mediators. Butylphthalide has been shown to protect against neurodegenerative diseases by reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in the brain. Ferulic acid has been found to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and scavenge free radicals, contributing to its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects. The combination of these constituents in Angelica sinensis makes it a valuable medicinal plant for promoting cardiovascular health, reducing inflammation and oxidative stress, and alleviating menopausal symptoms.",
