    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Angelica sinensis are derived from its root and are primarily used to promote women's health and alleviate menstrual issues. Dong quai tea is a traditional preparation made by steeping the dried root in hot water, often used to ease menstrual cramps and regulate menstrual cycles. Dong quai capsules are a standardized extract of the root, typically containing 10-20% ferulic acid, which has been shown to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Angelica sinensis tincture and angelica tincture are liquid extracts of the root, often used to treat menstrual disorders and menopausal symptoms due to their high content of isoflavones and ferulic acid. Dong quai extract is a concentrated form of the root's bioactive compounds, commonly used in pharmaceuticals and dietary supplements to alleviate menstrual irregularities and promote female reproductive health.",
